oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cambridge, Corpus Christi College, MS 296: John Wyclif and his followers, Tracts in Middle English
Tracts by Wyclif
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: CCCC MS 296 contains a late fourteenth-century (after 1383) collection of Lollard tracts and sermons written in Middle English. The entire collection was once ascribed to John Wyclif (d. 1384) but is now believed to be the work of a number of authors. All the tracts in this volume have been published by either F. D. Matthew in 1880 and 1902 (repr.1998) or Thomas Arnold in 1871.

physicalDescription.note: (3 flyleaves) a(8)-r(8) s(10) t(4): old pagination incorrect but used here.

The volume is a leading authority for many of the Wycliffite tracts, and was extensively used by F. D. Matthew, English Works of Wyclif (E. E. T. S. 1880) and by T. Arnold, Select English Works of Wyclif, vol. III.
f. iv. Extract from letter of Melanchthon to Fred. Miconius: Inspexi Wiclefum sed deprehendi, etc. (cf. MS 103. 5).
f. iiiv. Note given by Nasmith.
